"At independence Kenya's economic indicators were equal to those of South Korea,
but 45 years down the road, Korea's economy is 40 times that of Kenya. The
mediocrity of leadership is across the continent."

The mediocrity with which Africa has been ruled is responsible for its underdevelopment.
